article.headline: Fairfield 66, St. Peter's 58
article.story: BRIDGEPORT, Conn. (AP) -- Herbie Allen scored 19 points to lead Fairfield to a 66-58 win over St. Peter's Friday night. The Stags (7-15, 5-5 Metro Atlantic Athletic Conference) won their fourth straight to establish their longest winning streak in three seasons. Michael Van Schaick added 15 points for Fairfield, which won despite allowing St. Peter's to shoot 68.4 percent from the floor in the second half. Raul Orta's 13 points led the Peacocks (3-17, 1-9), who lost their 12th straight. Leading 47-46 with 8 minutes remaining in the second half, Fairfield seized control with an 11-3 burst over three minutes. The Stags outrebounded the Peacocks 27-23. The Stags missed their first eight shots of the game, but trailed only 7-3 after Jonathan Han nailed a 3-pointer to end the scoring drought. Mamadou Diakhate finished with 11 points for the Stags.
